description: From Ancient Greek ψῖ (psî), the name for the twenty-third letter of the alphabet (Ψ, ψ).

entries.meaning: (countable) The twenty-third letter of Classical and Modern Greek and the twenty-fifth letter of Old and Ancient Greek.
(uncountable, parapsychology) A form of psychic energy.
examples: ‘Come, lad,’ he said. ‘We will take tea together and speak of the noumenon, the psi and other more heterogenous phenomena.’

description: Initialism of pounds per square inch.
